& [SourceSet] is the checked research surface
  + [source_001] is Arapura and Kang, Known cases of the Hodge conjecture
    = url: https://ar5iv.labs.arxiv.org/html/2105.04695
    = relevance: surveys known cases and the Griffiths-Green approach, showing scoped success rather than arbitrary construction
  + [source_002] is Clay Mathematics Institute Hodge problem statement
    = url: https://www.claymath.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/hodge.pdf
    = relevance: preserves the formal target as rational Hodge classes on smooth projective complex varieties realized by algebraic cycles
  + [source_003] is Voisin, The Hodge conjecture
    = url: https://webusers.imj-prg.fr/~claire.voisin/Articlesweb/voisinhodge.pdf
    = relevance: explains the relation between topology, Hodge structure, and algebraic cycle realization
  + [source_004] is Griffiths, Hodge theory and geometry
    = url: https://publications.ias.edu/sites/default/files/hodgegeom.pdf
    = relevance: emphasizes that Hodge-theoretic assumptions require constructing geometric objects such as algebraic cycles
  + [source_005] is Voisin, Hodge and generalized Hodge conjectures, coniveau and algebraic cycles
    = url: https://webusers.imj-prg.fr/~claire.voisin/Articlesweb/JOMP_V01N01P02Paper.pdf
    = relevance: surveys Hodge/generalized Hodge, coniveau, motives, and cycle-related structures in modern form
  + [source_006] is Green-Voisin explicit Noether-Lefschetz theorem context
    = url: https://ullmo.ihes.fr/publications/voisinNL1.pdf
    = relevance: shows explicit Noether-Lefschetz structure as a special-locus detection framework
  + [source_007] is Relative Beilinson-Hodge normal-function framework
    = url: https://www.math.purdue.edu/~patel471/RelBeiHodge.pdf
    = relevance: clarifies generalized normal functions and the need for existence-type theorems rather than mere invariants

& [ResearchResolution] is the explicit-cycle/correspondence result
  + [confirmed_001_explicit_cycles_are_scoped] is explicit cycle construction is real in known cases and special geometries, but does not generalize as an arbitrary Hodge-class algorithm
  + [confirmed_002_correspondences_transfer_when_available] is algebraic correspondences can transport algebraicity, but they are extra structure rather than automatic output from an arbitrary rational Hodge class
  + [confirmed_003_noether_lefschetz_is_detection_not_general_construction] is Noether-Lefschetz methods locate special loci and extra algebraic classes, but do not construct cycles for arbitrary classes outside those loci
  + [confirmed_004_normal_functions_are_powerful_but_indirect] is normal functions and Abel-Jacobi-type tools organize obstructions and families, but still require an existence/construction theorem for cycles
  + [confirmed_005_substitute_theories_do_not_solve_clay_target] is motives, absolute Hodge, and related substitute structures may organize evidence but do not replace algebraic cycle output

